"John P. Kline" wrote:
> 
> A PIO card is not necessary, i.e. DMDX should run just fine without
> one.  You can run it with a keyboard or a mouse, although the polling times
> might leave something to be desired.  A standard joystick (in <Rawjoystick>
> mode) is a reasonable response box.
> 
> JK
> 
